ApiToken: Will be sent in a separate secured email

SubId: Below is the format accepted:

Traffic Type - Origin of the lead in full text (e.g. Search, Social, Google, Facebook, Taboola).

Specific campaign (if all leads come from a single platform) - Abbreviate the traffic type/platform and add a numerical value at the end (e.g FB1, FB2, FB3, GG1, GG2, TB1, TB2, EM1, EM2 etc).

Note: Avoid using the same 3 digits at the end

Avoid using special characters (e.g. semi-colons, (back)slashes, quotation marks, commas, etc.)

Avoid using formulas

The ID should not be unique to each lead (Max 20 different subId’s per account)

The use of the company name is not allowed

Specs: Please follow the instructions provided in the links below.

One-to-One Consent Leads (Brand Explicit Consent):

Sending the Match Ping (pre ping) : https://api.px.com/v2/verticals/match-ping/match-ping-leads/

only ping post: https://api.px.com/v2/verticals/auto/ping-post-exclusive-auto/

Sending the Post:

You will need to pass the BrandConsent and MatchPingId fields on the Post. You can find an example of this here: https://api.px.com/v2/verticals/match-ping/ping-post-leads-1/.
Note: The Match Ping → Post flow will only allow you to send one to one consent leads with this account.

Brand Explicit (One-to-One) Consent Form Flow: Could you share with us how you will be displaying the matched brand(s) in your form (ex: single brand in TCPA, multi-select of matched brands, multiple TCPAs...)?

Non One-to-One Consent Leads (Regular Ping Post):

Vertical Specific Requirements: https://api.px.com/v2/verticals/auto/ping-post-exclusive-auto/